  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Black, Indigenous, POC Sci-Fi Screenwriting Lab</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sci-Fi and Fantasy genres in mainstream Hollywood often leave Black, Indigenous, and People of Color (BIPOC) out of the equation. Justice for My Sister is raising funds to bring back our BIPOC Sci-Fi Screenwriting Lab in 2021. Our first edition gave a safe space to working adults committed to imagining ourselves into the future, powerfully. Their TV pilot scripts called on ancestral wisdom to course-correct climate change and incorporated critical race theory to paint a pathway to liberation.</narrative>
  </description>
